text: Örebro IK was an ice hockey team from Örebro, Sweden. It was founded in 1972.Eliteprospects.com. Örebro IK. Retrieved 2013-07-04. The team played elite-level hockey. The team became bankrupt and was liquidated in 1999. Today, Örebro is represented in Sweden's upper-tier hockey leagues by Örebro HK. ==Other websites== *Club profile on Eliteprospects.com ==References== Category:Ice hockey teams in Sweden Category:1972 establishments in Sweden Category:1999 disestablishments in Sweden
